The paper deals with person re-identification, which is a computer vision problem, hence it is likely to belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) category. The paper also proposes a new method for model generalization and adaptation, which involves designing a constraint over ReID feature, which is a machine learning technique, hence it is likely to belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) category. The paper also involves extensive experiments between three large datasets, which is related to multimedia, hence it is likely to belong to the cs.MM (Multimedia) category. The paper also involves domain adaptation, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence, hence it is likely to belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) category. Finally, the paper also involves improving alignment, which is related to cryptography, hence it is likely to belong to the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) category.
